divs: Sighting DetailsDuring my vacations the last summer (in Chile) and visiting the "Colbun lake" (35��� 42' 10.66" S 71��� 20' 28.25" W), near to Linares city in Chile, just in the middle day, a very warm day, no clouds, no birds, no sounds, it is means a very calm moment, we (my wife and me) were taken photos to the Colbun lake from the southern side of lake with north side on view and few minutus later revising the images, appear clearly an objet with a disk shape. At first sight, this object does no look like a plane or bird, is clearly a solid objet floating in the sky, the second photo show the same objet far in the sky, apparently flying to the north.
trends: There have been no other sightings in Linares

Summary: Disk shape object appear on photo.
